The chorus of excited dragon calls confirms Merenth's guess.  They all want a shot.  Almost as if they had practiced, they swept down one by one to tear at him, the last one being one streak of glittering ruby and sky blue, coming down hard enough to snap an arm and tear off a hand.  Corathin.  Thrain was left bloody and gasping in pain , from the acid in his skull and the damage from hundreds of dragon claws.  Corathin hovered over him briefly, glaring.<br>
