<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Dark lords are not immortal.  They simply have enough power to make it seem that way.  And they simply tend to live obscenely long lives. Unless they are killed.  We gave you the chance to flee yet you elected to stay here and face our wrath.  Your time is up.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
With that, she launches herself in that short distance to Thrain, the light from her claw turning red as she draws nearer.  Her mute spell is removed as she roars, descending.  Thrain, hearing this, screams in fear, but it is cut off.  Merenth's wings cup around him as her spell tears him to shreds.  The dragons above scream triumph when their queen's wings noticeably darken, the mage's blood oozing slowly from under them.  Merenth raises her head high, her nose blotched red, and opens her wings to show nothing more than a bloody mess where Thrain once stood.  Her right claw is bloody and dotted in tiny whitish bits.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;We warned him.  Prentieth, tell the Dark one that we're coming for him.  When the time comes.  Return to me soon, brother.  I'm sorry...  You'll have your release when I set my eyes on your silver horns again...&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">&quot;I know.  I'll be around.  Just don't take too long, Merenth.  Sapphire scales have been stained with their bearer's blood for too long...&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Thousands of years...  Too long...  I'll see you later.  And speak with you sooner.  Together we'll flay him.  Brother.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
